Description:
    Generates a Strata::Task subclass with standardized templates and automatically checks for the strata_tasks table.

Usage:
    bin/rails generate strata:task NAME [options]

Examples:
    bin/rails generate strata:task ReviewApplication
    bin/rails generate strata:task ProcessPayment --parent CustomTask
    bin/rails generate strata:task DataEntry --skip-migration-check

Options:
    --parent CLASS_NAME: Custom parent class name (optional)
        Default: Strata::Task
        Example: --parent CustomTaskBase

    --skip-migration-check: Skip checking if strata_tasks table exists (optional)
        Default: false
        Example: --skip-migration-check

This will create:
    A task class file at app/models/{name}_task.rb inheriting from the specified parent class (default: Strata::Task)
    A corresponding RSpec test file at spec/models/{name}_task_spec.rb
    Automatically checks for strata_tasks table existence and prompts to install and run Strata migrations if needed (unless --skip-migration-check is used)
